                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> If the snared guard was too close to the other one after it reset, you are just FDing too soon. You need to allow enough time for the guard to walk out of aggro range of the reset add. Snare, and run a bit before FDing - that will fix it. Obviously, the trick is to balance things out. Wait too long and your DD will break before other guard resets.</span id="msg"></font></td>
