                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Yup just wait longer to FD and he'll be far enough away that he won't aggro the other one.  Also note that the pathing can be a bit odd at times where the snared one will path back towards where he started and THEN come back towards you, aggroing the second guard again.  The way to resolve this is to move closer to the snared guard.  This works because, while mobs will rely upon pathing if you are far away (say at max spell casting distance), if you are close enough (and the relevant distance is further than the mob's melee distance so no fear of getting hit) they will make a beeline towards you regardless of pathing.</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
