                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> ok ok ok <br /><br />sarky head off<br /><br />on top of what the others said<br /><br />in 90% of cases when a mob returns to its spawn spot (assuming static pops like all basements mobs are) it'll forget you<br /><br />soooo<br /><br />1 snare 1 mob<br />2 run away<br />3 once snared mob is a good bit from its spawn spot FD<br />4 the 2 mobs will turn to walk back to spawn<br />5 the UNsnared 1 will walk back as normal,the snared 1 will stand still<br />6 when the unsnared 1 is back at spawn , stand up to check aggro<br />7 only the snared 1 (assuming its out of range of the other) will come to you<br /><br />VOILA, you've snare-split 2 mobs..<br /><br />not to patronize you but try it on 2 REALLY easy mobs to sorta perfect the technique<br /><br />still staggered you've never used/heard of/seen this technique before though...<br /><br />good luck</span id="msg"></font></td>
