                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> When I first started kiting in hoh crypts I would ignore sides of the room if two sentries were there when I started because I couldn't split them.<br /><br />After some experience and some gumption I learned that if you can kite one sentry you can kite two.  It will take a bit of time but here's what I do:<br /><br />1) I use an AH4 item and a ER4 item and SOW.  Stand at max casting range and cast BOT on one of the sentries. <br /><br />2) Run like a little scaredy cat until BOT refrehses. Cast BOT on 2nd sentry. Sic pet on 2nd sentry.<br /><br />3) Run like a little scaredy cat. Cast horror, FP, and refresh BOT as needed. Repeat.<br /><br />4) Use TOM to fill up Hitpoints as needed.<br /><br />5) Don't get hit.<br /><br />Kermit</span id="msg"></font></td>
