                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Well depending on which spawn the sentry was you know whether or not you have a chance at fighting into respawn time.  For me it would only be possible if sentry spawns as first mob you pulled.  I Alternate the clearing 1 from each first so I never have to split em again, even if I get slowed down by a sentry.<br /><br />Also, have you noticed that when you land a dot in HoH the mob gets kinda stunned for a split second.  It throws its arms up in the air and shakes(great description there).  You use that split second after casting to straphe away.  Also running around the columns in the corner helps.<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
